commit.message: Added warning when using RTD together with BuilderManyBody.
Merge branch 'real_time_diagrammatics' of https://github.com/gedaskir/qmeq into real_time_diagrammatics
Changed indexing of Tba in RTD approach to be consistent with other approaches.

Use GitHub Actions and cibuildwheel to build wheels.

Other misc things:
1. Remove AppVeyor and Travis integration.
2. Introduce pyproject.yml
3. Use only setuptools in setup.py (remove distutils).
4. Get rid of NumPy deprecation warning by changing np.int to int.
Remove 'DeprecationWarning: invalid escape sequence \' by using raw strings.

Add a changelog for upcoming release 1.1.

Modify the documentation a bit to better reflect the state of the code.
Updated documentation. Added docstrings to most functions in kernel_handler.
Added support for models that give rise to complex matrix elements.
Add OpenMP support for first-order aprroaches and RTD approach.

Add Martin Josefsson and Martin Leijnse to the author list.

The names are listed in alphabetical order of surenames.

Python 2.7 support is removed so  __future__ statements are no longer needed.

Also clean up the trailing spaces.
Fixed a typo introduced in the previous commit.
Updated energy cutoffs for tunnel matrix elements and energies (in integrals).
Prepared the RTD approach for parallelization using OpenMP.
Changed some string- and number comparisons in tests to avoid error messages in python3.8
Updated the file structure for the documentation.

commit.message: changed line 795 of qdot.py
Added the new second order approaches RTD and pyRTD (for real time diagrammatics). The RTD approach provides an efficient way of dealing with diagonal density matrices in second order.
User KernelHandler state indexing in Cython implementation of the Approach2vN class.
Introduce TermsCalculator2vN class.

Refactor Approach2vN class.

Move majority of methods into the class body.
Reuse some arrays.

Change method names:
  kern_2vN -> generate_kern
  get_phi1_phi -> determine_phi1_ph0
  get_emin_emax -> determine_emin_emax
  get_grid_ext -> determine_grid_ext

Introduce methods:
  prepare_energy_grid
  prepare_distribution

Reuse methods from the Approach class:
  restart
  prepare_kern
  prepare_arrays
  clean_arrays

Clean-up: do not use [self.] in docstrings.
Add regions in the Approach class. Move the code a bit around.
Extract KernelHandler classes to separate files.
Move types to wrappers folder.

Introduce possibility to make a copy of an array in LAPACK solvers.

Introduce a property make_kern_copy.
Call LAPACK solvers through SciPy Cython wrappers.
Add properties to the Approach class. Reuse dphi0_dt array.
Reuse some arrays for QuantumDot, LeadsTunneling, and PhononBaths classes.
